The paper discusses neural network models for dynamic systems, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also compares two different training methods and evaluates their computational cost, convergence, and robustness, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions stability properties, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY), and includes an example using measured data, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
